comments.author: Josh Reyes

comments.text:
+Matt Jaskol I never had a tandem before my AFF so thats not quite true, 
there are dropzones that require you to do a tandem first as part of their 
specific training but most dropzones I know of allow you to go straight 
into the first level of AFF.

As for Josh, if he haven't done one yet and still wonder about his heart 
condition, the rules for skydiving as far as health goes requires you to 
pass a doctor examining you through a specific "skydive" examination that 
covers the general health aspects relevant to high altitudes, stress 
situations and adrenaline as far as I remember, along with the doctors own 
judgement on any other conditions (like your heart condition).


But as long as you don't have a risk of going unconcious/seizure I think, 
in my non-doctor-but-skydive experiance that you will be allowed to, so it 
really is just to ask the dropzone for the examination papers and then 
visit your doctor.

comments.author: Cielo Gomez

comments.text:
Published on June 19, 2014
Red Bull never ceases to amaze us with their high-impact, exhilarating 
videos featuring stunts we’d probably think twice about attempting.

First, we watched Felix Baumgartner jump from the edge of space, now Red 
Bull continues to pull off insane stunts by capturing footage of two 
“skydive extraordinaires” who go by the names of Fred Fugen and Vince 
Reffet.

The daredevil duo teamed up to skydive from the edge of the atmosphere 
10,000 meters above Mt. Blanc. According to the video’s description, that’s 
the limit that a human can go without wearing a pressurized suit.

These dudes really pushed the limit here. So far, the video managed to rack 
up over 47,000 views in one day. You’re just going to have to see it to 
believe it!﻿
